# No AI agent attribution

Never leave traces of AI tooling in the repository.

## Code comments

Do not add comments that mention AI agents, assistants, or codegen tools — for example Cursor, Claude, Copilot, ChatGPT, "AI-generated", "written by an agent", or similar.

Comments must explain **code behavior only**, not how the change was produced.

```java
// BAD: added by Cursor to fix zombie targeting
// BAD: AI suggested this approach

// GOOD: TACZ gun hits may not set DamageSource.getEntity(); retaliate via event
```

## Commits, docs, and releases

- No `Co-authored-by` or agent/tool attribution in commit messages.
- No AI attribution in README, AGENTS.md, release notes, or other docs unless the user explicitly asks for agent documentation.

## When editing existing comments

If you touch a file, remove any AI-attribution comments you find — do not preserve or extend them.
